    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-09-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-09-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="297"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d297">
                <head>297. Telegram From the Mission to the United Nations to the Department of
                        State<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d297fn1">Source: Department of State,
                        Central Files, 770G.00/9–2562. Confidential. Received on September 26 at
                        1:10 a.m. and repeated to Léopoldville, Brussels, Paris, and London.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>New York</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1962-09-25">September 25, 1962</date>, midnight.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>905. Congo. During <persName corresp="#p_CWY1">Yost</persName> call on <persName
                        corresp="#p_RJB1">Bunche</persName> this afternoon latter described meeting
                    between <persName corresp="#p_PHS1">Spaak</persName> and <gloss target="#SYG1"
                        >SYG</gloss> on Congo at which it agreed that <persName corresp="#p_MT1"
                        >Tshombe</persName> unlikely implement reconciliation plan unless he forced
                    to do so. <persName corresp="#p_RJB1">Bunche</persName> had suggested and others
                    agreed that only cut-off of <gloss target="#UMHK1">UMHK</gloss> payments to
                        <persName corresp="#p_MT1">Tshombe</persName> could force him to cooperate.
                    As result, <persName corresp="#p_RJB1">Bunche</persName> had drafted and sent to
                        <persName corresp="#p_RKAG1">Gardiner</persName> cable setting forth this
                    view and submitting for <persName corresp="#p_RKAG1">Gardiner</persName>’s
                    comments following proposal: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>PriMin <persName corresp="#p_CA1">Adoula</persName> would send letter
                            to <gloss target="#UMHK1">UMHK</gloss> notifying it that he expected all
                                <gloss target="#UMHK1">UMHK</gloss> payments be made directly to
                            GOC.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>PriMin would have Congo Parliament pass legislation requiring that all
                            payments by mining companies be made directly to GOC.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>PriMin would send letter to Belgian Government asking it to assure
                                <gloss target="#UMHK1">UMHK</gloss> compliance with new law.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#SYG1">SYG</gloss> would send letter to appropriate
                                <gloss target="#UN1">UN</gloss> member states eliciting their help
                            in obtaining compliance with law.</item>
                        <label>5.</label>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#SYG1">SYG</gloss> would go to <gloss target="#SC1"
                                >SC</gloss> with request for approval his action and asking for
                            specific authority to guard <gloss target="#UMHK1">UMHK</gloss>
                            installations.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_RJB1">Bunche</persName> was very pessimistic over
                        <persName corresp="#p_MT1">Tshombe</persName>’s attitude. Cited as two
                    recent indications of it the unreasonable line taken by <persName
                        corresp="#p_MT1">Tshombe</persName>’s representative in military commission
                    and deliberate mining by Katangese of route traveled by Gurkha patrol. Said
                    Katanga military commission rep had demanded that <gloss target="#UN1"
                        >UN</gloss> evacuate Elizabethville airfield. Charged that mine which killed
                    Gurkhas had been touched off when they were retracing route they had just
                    successfully traversed.</p>
                <pb facs="0615" n="587" xml:id="pg_587"/>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_RJB1">Bunche</persName> said he had asked <gloss
                        target="#SYG1">SYG</gloss> what he would do if plan failed. <gloss
                        target="#SYG1">SYG</gloss> had replied he would go to <gloss target="#SC1"
                        >SC</gloss> and ask for authority to withdraw from Congo. <persName
                        corresp="#p_RJB1">Bunche</persName> said he had told <gloss target="#SYG1"
                        >SYG</gloss> he could not obtain votes in <gloss target="#SC1">SC</gloss>
                    for passage such resolution.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AES1">Stevenson</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
